title: Chang’e-6 spacecraft dock in lunar orbit ahead of journey back to Earth
summary: An ascent vehicle docked with the Chang’e-6 service module Thursday, in a critical step towards bringing the first lunar far side samples to Earth.

title: Astroscale shares soar in Tokyo stock market debut
summary: Shares in satellite servicing and debris removal company Astroscale jumped in the first day of trading on the Tokyo Stock Exchange June 5, giving the company a valuation of about $1 billion.

title: First Ariane 6 launch set for July 9
summary: The European Space Agency and its partners have announced a July 9 launch date for the first Ariane 6 rocket.

title: SES tests MEO-LEO data relay capability

title: Starship Gets Ready to Launch for a Fourth Time
summary:
SpaceX is preparing to launch the fourth flight of Starship on Thursday, during a two-hour window that opens at 7 AM central time. Booster 11 and Ship 29 are the pairing for the latest test flight, with primary goals of a pinpoint soft water landing for the Booster, and additional re-entry data for the Ship.
